How

Embark on the Transdisciplinary Journey

Enter the TRAIL: a comprehensive tool crafted to illuminate the pivotal stages of transdisciplinary collaboration, drawing upon extensive scientific research and practical insights from experts, students, policymakers, educators, and societal partners. Within the Trail, well delve into the diverse aspects and phases of creating, participating in, and evaluating transdisciplinary education.

Begin your expedition at the BASE CAMP, where youll assemble with your expedition team and acquire essential knowledge on fostering successful collaborations across diverse backgrounds.


Advance to the next phase: DESIGNING the transdisciplinary education. Delve into the intricacies of co-creating projects and cultivating fruitful learning environments, nurturing growth and development for all involved.


Arrive at the DESIGN RESEARCH STATION, also known as LOWER CAMP, where youll reflect on your journey, engage in research, and contribute to the further refinement of the TRAIL TOOL. Extend invitations to others interested in joining your expedition team, enriching the collaborative experience.

Transition to the PARTICIPATION phase, where youll explore effective learning strategies, organizational methods, and communication techniques. A tip- if you are not interested right now in the Design Phase, you can take a shortcut from a Base Camp directly to the Participation Path. Rest and reflect at UPPER CAMP post-Participation, integrating newfound insights and preparing for the final ascent towards the summit. Here, collective efforts converge into a COMMON GOAL, fostering success, impactful planning, and lasting relationships.


Upon reaching the summit, celebrate the wealth of experiences, knowledge, and accomplishments achieved with your expedition team. Reflect on the journey through a structured evaluation process, ensuring meaningful growth and learning.


Welcome to the TRAIL an exhilarating adventure awaits! Join us at the BASE CAMP for the next phase of discovery with your expedition team.
